comments: Smith Jr. (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as contact is made with Osman (CLE) during the drive, then makes marginal contact with Osman's left hand that does not affect his ability to pass.
[Observable in enhanced video] Osman (CLE) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Osman (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Sexton (CLE) makes marginal contact with Smith Jr.'s (NYK) front at the end of the drive that does not affect his SQBR.

Trier (NYK) veers into Clarkson's (CLE) path and initiates body contact that affects his SQBR. The crew communicated with the Replay Center to determine if the foul by Trier (NYK) met the criteria for a clear path foul. After review, it was determined that Trier would be assessed a clear path foul.
Knox (NYK) makes marginal contact with Sexton's (CLE) left arm at the end of the drive, which does not affect his ability to gather or pass the ball.
LLS shows Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in a wide screening position in Sexton's (CLE) path and some foot-to-foot contact occurs, but it does not affect Sexton's ability to defend.
Robinson (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Sexton's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Zizic (CLE) makes incidental contact with Knox (NYK) during rebounding.
Clarkson (CLE) makes marginal contact with Trier's (NYK) front that does not affect his SQBR during the drive.
Osman (CLE) cleanly strips Knox (NYK) of the ball during his upward shooting motion.
Knox (NYK) legally re-gains control of the ball after it is dislodged and starts his dribble.
Robinson (NYK) initiates contact with Sexton's (CLE) upper half, affecting his FOM.
Zizic (CLE) clamps and holds Robinson's (NYK) arm, affecting his ability to get to the rebound.
Ellenson (NYK) makes incidental contact with Zizics (CLE) face/head area during his legal attempt to reach the loose ball.
[Observable in enhanced video] Trier (NYK) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Love (CLE) maintains legal guarding position and absorbs the contact made with Trier (NYK) during the driving shot attempt.

LAR shows Robinson (NYK) makes slight contact with Love's (CLE) right wrist after making initial contact with the ball during rebounding, but it is marginal and does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
RLS shows Clarkson (CLE) legally contests Knox's (NYK) jump shot attempt.

LLS shows Love (CLE) makes incidental contact with Robinson's (NYK) wrist after making clean contact with the ball during rebounding. The crew communicated with the Replay Center to determine who the ball went out of bounds off of. Initially, possession was awarded to NYK, and after review, the ruling was overturned to CLE ball.
Robinson (NYK) commits the take foul on Love (CLE).
Nwaba (CLE) makes clean contact with the ball prior to incidental contact being made with Trier's (NYK) front thereafter.
Robinson (NYK) commits the take foul on Love (CLE).
[Observable in enhanced video] Mudiay (NYK) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot to the floor prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.
Robinson (NYK) makes brief contact with Love's (CLE) right arm during rebounding, but it is marginal and does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Nwaba (CLE) absorbs the contact made with Trier (NYK) during his shot attempt near the rim.
Nwaba (CLE) initiates body/arm contact with Trier (NYK) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Robinson (NYK) commits the take foul on Love (CLE).
Love (CLE) briefly has his hands on Smith Jr.'s (NYK) upper-half before correcting.
